Summary: 
On January 20, 2021, President Donald Trump issued an executive order revoking Executive Order 13770, which pertained to ethics commitments by executive branch appointees. The revocation is effective as of noon on January 20, 2021, and employees and former employees subject to the commitments in the previous executive order will no longer be bound by them. The order clarifies that it does not affect the authority of executive departments or agencies, or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It also states that the order should be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations. Lastly, the order states that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.